name: Twiddley Diddley
description:
Artisan jeweler.
Originally from Dwyar Valur, Twiddley found he was not fond of the mining and the brutalist architecture and aesthetics of their craft. Instead he enjoyed making finer, more delicate and mechanical things. He moved to the capital city of Kenser where he opened an artisan jewelry shop making quite the name for himself.
Although he does not align with their beliefs, he has dealt with members of the Red Order as they have presented him with rare gemstones: the casting stones. He has garnered quite the rapport with them as one of the few who are willing to work with them.
Twiddley pursues further perfecting his craft, creating more delicate and complex pieces.
He's not one for violence, but understands it comes with the territory so his weapon of choice is a pistol as it piques his craftsman interests. The fine mechanisms of it are fascinating.
Through work he has come to know several people in Kenser, forming bonds and friendships.

skills.name: Riding - Novice - 0
skills.description:
Mounted Individuals Gain These Abilities:
Mounted: This character is mounted on horseback and thus has gained the following abilities: 

Riding Speed: Movement speed while mounted is double normal speed

Trample: Target up to 3 enemies within a 5 foot radius of each other and charge them at full speed. In addition to any charge attack made while mounted you can trample up to 3 additional targets. If successful targets each take D% as Blunt Physical Damage.
Uses Str + roll for accuracy 
Unskilled: D10-2
Novice: D10
Skilled: D10+2

Mounted Attack: All melee attacks from a mounted position towards unmounted targets have their damage doubled. Attacks on other mounted targets deal normal damage.

skills.name: Pistol - Skilled - 1
skills.description: Skilled: +1 to roll when shooting, grants Advanced Quickdraw (no debuff to quickdraw), doubleshot (can use both actions to fire)

skills.name: General Magic - Novice*
skills.description:
Detect Magic: Sense magic items, enemies, and powers. Able to identify the type of magic force or exact spell used. 
Cost: None
Cast time: Instant

Charge Weapon: Imbues weapon with magic damage or armor/shields with magic resistance equal to 2 x Int for 3 turns. After 3 turns the weapon dissolves into ash. 
Cost: 2 charges.
Cast time: 2 actions

Illuminate: Create small light in one’s hand, have to have one hand free
Cost: 0 charges. 
Cast time: 0 actions

Flash of light: Blind foes facing you up to 10 feet in front of you. Blind lasts 1 turn.
Cost: 1 charge
Cast time: Instant

skills.name: Scholarly Magic - Skilled*
skills.description:
Understand Magic: Any magical items, enemies, or phenomena within reason must be explained to this player if they choose to analyze it. 

Forge Enchanted Weapon: Player may devote one week’s time to smith/forge any type of weapon (with appropriate amount of resources) along with any magical item to create an Enchanted Weapon. The weapon will be the same as its melee counterpart only with the added magical damage of the forging players int x 3 and any additional effects the magical item may give built into the weapon. 

Allows socketing: Player may fuse a magical item or gemstone into a socketable weapon or piece of armor, giving it the effects of said magical item. 

+3 INT

skills.name: Fire Magic - Skilled - 1
skills.description:
Wall of Flame: Create a curtain of flame 20 feet long. All targets that cross the wall must pass a medium agility check or take the Burning status effect. 
Range: 20 feet
Cost: 2 charges to cast, 1 charge to maintain
Cast Time: 1 action, channeled

Channel Flame: Create a stream of fire from your hands coming out in a stream, enemies and allies caught in it will be on fire, and also lights flammable objects on fire as well. 
Range: 10 feet
Cost: 1 charge per action
Cast Time: 1 action, channeled

Wave of Fire: Generate a wave of flame behind your hand, sending a roiling torrent of flame crashing into your enemy. 
Range: 5 feet
Cost: 4 charges
Cast Time: Instant

Heat Blast: Cause a blast of extreme heat to go directly in front of you knocking all non massive characters down and back 5 feet.
Range: 5 feet
Cost: 3 charges
Cast Time: Instant 

Cataclysm (Fire): Self-destruct in a massive explosion 30 feet in diameter causing int x D12 magic damage knockdown and igniting area on fire for 2 turns, kills character and leaves only a crater where they remain.
Range: Self
Cost: 6 charges
Cast Time: 6 action cast

skills.description:
Minor Skill
+1 to intimidation rolls

Intimidate: Roll D8+PRE vs opponent's D10+PRE or INT. If successful, opponent suffers -2 initiative and may only use 1 action next turn.

Range: Self
Cost: 2 charges
